  "texts": [
    "Only the interval in which it is approximated, i.e.",
    "the parameter K, affects the failure probability.",
    "If ∥I(Y)∥ > K, then the EvalMod step returns an unusable corrupted plaintext.",
    "This failure probability is defined as f fail (K, h, M) = Pr [∥I(Y)∥ > K] by [BTH22] and they show how to compute it by adapting the Irwin Hall cumulative distribution function:",
    "(1) Usually the bootstrapping parameters are instantiated using a secret with fixed Hamming weight h, which allows to get an exact estimation of f fail (K, h, M), and thus to choose K according to the desired failure probability."
